# Cursor rules — Virtual Card Lifecycle

Source of truth: `specifications/ai/AGENTS.md` + `specifications/product/specs/001-feature/spec.md`.
This file is the condensed, always-on guardrail set. When in doubt, open the spec/ADRs.

## Non-negotiables (regulated FinTech)
- Money = integer **minor units** / `Decimal`, one currency per card, compared in minor units. No `float`.
- Only `network_token` + `last4` — **never** PAN/CVV anywhere (code, logs, traces, tests, URLs).
- State changes: single state-machine fn, legal transitions only (BR-001/002), `CLOSED` terminal.
- Writes: **idempotent** (`Idempotency-Key`) + **optimistic concurrency** (`If-Match`/ETag).
- Every state change → one **audit event** in the same transaction (outbox); no exceptions.
- **Deny by default**, separation of duties; SCA + role for close / lifting compliance freeze.
- **Fail closed** on ambiguity or dependency loss; stable error codes; no sensitive detail in errors.

## Style
- `mypy --strict`, Pydantic at boundaries, UTC ISO-8601, opaque UUIDv7/ULID ids.
- Conventional Commits + task id (`feat: … (T-0xx)`); one task per PR from `delivery/tasks.md`.
- Propose a test (mapped to an FR / edge case E-xx) with nontrivial code; self-verify ruff→mypy→pytest.

## Avoid
Bypassing idempotency/concurrency/audit/state-machine; scope creep; silent contract/requirement
changes (needs an ADR); secrets in code; UPDATE/DELETE on `audit_events`.
